      <Button>Fiscal Overview</Button>
      <Description>
        <![CDATA[<p style='line-height:1.5'>The table shows <b><span
style='color:#0070C0'>total annual amounts </span></b>of the specified
tax-benefit system(s). It provides an overview of market incomes as well as
government revenue and expenditure covered in EUROMOD. </p>

<p style='line-height:1.5'>The aggregated amount for “other
social insurance contributions” is already included in “employee social insurance
contributions” in all EM versions released before 2018.</p>
<p>Results refer to the following income lists:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Total market incomes: ils_origy</li>
	<li>Income from (self) employment: ils_earns</li>
	<li>Other market incomes: ils_origy minus ils_earns</li>
	<li>Government revenue through taxes and social insurance contributions are the sum of:
		<ul>
			<li>Direct taxes: ils_tax</li>
			<li>Employee social insurance contributions: ils_sicee</li>
			<li>Self-employed social insurance contributions: ils_sicse</li>
			<li>Other social insurance contributions: ils_sicot</li>
			<li>Employer social insurance contributions (not part of disposable income): ils_sicer</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Credited social insurance contributions (not part of disposable income): ils_sicct</li>
	<li>Government expenditure on social transfers: ils_ben <br>Which is the sum of:
		<ul>
			<li>Unemployment benefits: ils_b1_bun</li>
			<li>Family and education benefits: ils_b2_bfaed</li>
			<li>Social assistance and housing benefits: ils_b2_bsaho</li>
			<li>Pensions, health and disability benefits: ils_b2_penhl</li>
		</ul>
		As well as the sum of:
		<ul>
			<li>Means-tested non-pension benefits: ils_benmt</li>
			<li>Non-means-tested non-pension benefits: ils_bennt</li>
			<li>Pensions: ils_pen</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>
]]></Description>
